rows.label: qst200218_msg0001
rows.name:
If we wait here,
Harghal will appear, right?

rows.label: qst200218_msg0005
rows.name: You don't mean we were tricked?

rows.label: qst200218_msg0017
rows.name:
Maybe she's trying not to show herself
unless it's absolutely necessary.

rows.label: qst200218_msg0007
rows.name:
Well, at times like this,
rely on an informant, huh.

rows.label: qst200218_msg0008
rows.name:
In that case,
the Black Market in Teos Aure.

rows.label: qst200218_msg0010
rows.name:
Black Market, huh[ML:Dash ] Villains are doing
business there, right? Is it okay if I
bring down the iron hammer of justice?

rows.label: qst200218_msg0011
rows.name: Are you stupid? What are you saying!

rows.label: qst200218_msg0012
rows.name:
No good, no good, Glen.
It has the word "Dark/Black" attached,
but it's not that bad of a thing.

rows.label: qst200218_msg0013
rows.name:
If the Black Market disappeared from
Teos Aure, the people of Luxuria really
would starve to death.

rows.label: qst200218_msg0015
rows.name:
That's right. Even normal people do
business there. Just that official
 permission hasn't been granted.

rows.label: qst200218_msg0016
rows.name:
A necessary evil for people
to survive, huh[ML:Dash ]
